  • Constructor Details

    • User

      public User(String userName, String email, String password)
      This constructs a user with a specified username, email and password. Afterwards, from the email of the user, we will attain the user's userid which is the component in the email before '@'. We also attain all of the request that is directed or send out by the user based on his username through the use of another class method and put it in user's request list.
      Parameters:
      userName - the username of the user.
      email - the email of the user.
      password - the password of the user.

  • Method Details

      public void printPendingRequest()

    • addRequest

      public void addRequest(Request r)
      This method will add a new request object into the user's request list.
      Parameters:
      r - This is the new request object.

    • pendingRequest

      public boolean pendingRequest()
      This method checks for in the user's request list, does the user have any pending request that is requires his attention and input. Note that this is only applicable to the requests that is directed to the user, not send out by the user.
      Returns:
      true of false boolean value depending on if there is any pending request directed to the user.

    • getRequest

      public Request getRequest(int requestID)
      This method gets the request that is in the user's request list based on what is the request id inputted. If such a request id is not found in the user's request list, it will get nothing.
      Parameters:
      requestID - This is the value of the request id that you want to get back.
      Returns:
      the request object of the specificed request id.
